revision.text:
'''Charles Arthur Hollick''' (February 6, 1857 – March 11, 1933), known widely as '''Arthur Hollick''',<ref>{{cite book|last1= Stafleu|first1=Frans A.|last2=Cowan|first2=Richard S.|contribution=Hollick, [Charles] Arthur|title=Taxonomic Literature|volume=2|year=1979|pages=256–257}}</ref> was an American [[paleobotany|paleobotanist]]. He was curator of fossil plants at [[Columbia University]] and the [[New York Botanical Garden]]. Born in [[New Brighton, Staten Island]], New York, he received a [[Bachelor of Philosophy]] from [[Columbia School of Mines]] in 1879 and his doctorate at [[George Washington University]] (then known Columbian College) in 1897.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Howe|first1=Marshall A.|title=Arthur Hollick: February 6, 1857 – March 11, 1933|journal=Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club|date=November 1933|volume=60|issue=8|pages=537|doi=10.2307/2480533|jstor=2480533}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Arthur Hollick: 1857–1933
|first=E. C.|last= Jeffrey|journal=Science|volume=77|number=2002|date=May 12, 1933|pages=440–441|jstor=1656963}}</ref>  {{botanist|Hollick|inline=y}}

