{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Film Archive |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1978 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.bfa.gov.bd/ Bangladesh Film Archive] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Film Archive''' independent institution that is the national film archive of Bangladesh and preserves films, commercials and other visual medias produced in Bangladesh and is located in [[Shahbagh]], [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="qaz">{{cite web|last1=Hayat|first1=Anupam|title=Film Archive|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Film_Archive|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh Film Archive moves to new building|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-43876|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=29 October 2016|date=3 July 2008}}</ref>
==History== The Archive was established in 1978 by the government of Bangladesh. In 1984 it was made an independent institution.<ref name="qaz"></ref> In 2016 the archive donated [[Pramathesh Barua]]'s `[[Devdas]]' original print to India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangla to gift India print of Barua's Bengali 'Devdas'|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/Bangla-to-gift-India-print-of-Baruas-Bengali-Devdas/articleshow/54666646.cms|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref>
