'''''Standard Korean Language Dictionary''''' ({{Korean|hangul=표준국어대사전|hanja=標準國語大辭典|rr=pyojun-gugeo-dae-sajeon|mr=p'yojun-kugǒ-tae-sajǒn|links=|labels=|context=|lit="standard national language unabridged dictionary"}}) is a dictionary of the [[Korean language]], published by the [[National Institute of Korean Language]].
== History == The compilation of Standard Korean Language Dictionary was commenced on 1 January 1992, by [[The National Academy of the Korean Language]], the predecessor of the [[National Institute of Korean Language]].<ref name="nikl_en">{{cite web|title=History|url=http://www.korean.go.kr/front_eng/intro/intro_03.do|website=[[National Institute of Korean Language]]|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref> The dictionary's first edition was published in three volumes on 9 October 1999, followed by the [[compact disc]] released on 9 October 2001.<ref name="nikl_ko">{{link language|ko}} {{cite web|title=발자취|url=http://www.korean.go.kr/front/page/pageView.do?page_id=P000166&mn_id=74|website=[[National Institute of Korean Language]]|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref> The online dictionary was launched on 9 October 2002,<ref name="nikl_ko" /> and revised on 9 October 2008.<ref name="nikl_en" />
